President Donald Trump has announced his intent to nominate four individuals for judicial positions. David W. Dugan of Illinois is nominated to serve as Judge on the United States District Court for the Southern District of Illinois. Dugan is currently a Circuit Judge for the 3rd Judicial Circuit in Madison County, Illinois, and previously worked in private practice focusing on personal injury and commercial litigation. Iain D. Johnston, also from Illinois, is nominated to serve as Judge on the United States District Court for the Northern District of Illinois. Johnston is currently a United States Magistrate Judge and has experience in the Office of the Illinois Attorney General and private practice. Franklin U. Valderrama, also from Illinois, is nominated to serve as Judge on the United States District Court for the Northern District of Illinois. Valderrama is currently an Associate Judge in the Circuit Court of Cook County and has experience in trial litigation. Christy Criswell Wiegand of Pennsylvania is nominated to serve as Judge on the United States District Court for the Western District of Pennsylvania. Wiegand is currently an Assistant United States Attorney and has prosecuted various crimes, including drug trafficking and fraud.